replies.bodyText:
I'm in favor of an info log with a specific message, not the exception, and keep the exception as 2nd argument for the stack.
Also, we can have something like this (but overkill IMHO):
if (log.isInfoEnabled()) {
    log.info("message", e);
} else {
    log.warn("message");
}

timeline.bodyText:
You could use this:
org.nuxeo.common.utils.ExceptionUtils.checkInterrupt(e);
and get rid of these three lines + if / else.

